<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="link text-sm">← Use-case playbooks</a>
      <span class="badge mt-6">Marketing stack playbook</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Shopify marketing stack for {useCaseName}</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">{heroSubtitle}</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-300">Trigger: {trigger} · Timing: {timing}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title={`Stack picks for ${useCaseName}`} picks={tldrPicks} />
    <article class="prose-shopify mb-12 card">
      <h2>Stack execution playbook</h2>
  <p>Replenishment reminders are the profit engine for beauty, supplements, pet food, coffee, and consumable brands — but only when timed to actual consumption, gated on subscription status, and coordinated with loyalty and promotional layers. A universal 30-day reminder is the most common stack failure across consumable verticals.</p>
  <p>Trigger: days since last purchase of consumable SKU exceeds 80% of expected consumption window. Follow-up at 100% depletion; subscription upsell at 120% for non-subscribers only. Windows vary: serum 42 days, protein 30 days, dog food by weight math, coffee by bag size quiz.</p>
  <p>Recharge/Skio suppression is mandatory — active subscriber on same SKU must never receive single-purchase replenishment promo. Skip-flow subscribers get save branch, not replenishment. This collision destroys subscription trust weekly when unchecked.</p>
  <p>Full-price replenishment is the target KPI — defaulting to 10% off every reminder trains wait-for-code behavior. Incentive only on email two for lapsed replenishment responders; full-price loyalists get one-tap reorder deep link only.</p>
  <p>Bundle complexity: kit buyers deplete SKUs at different rates. Stack logic tracks line-item consumption separately — serum runs out before moisturizer in same kit order. Klaviyo properties updated per SKU purchase history.</p>
  <p>Privy consumption quiz at capture feeds timing math before first purchase even happens — household coffee consumption, pet weight, skin routine steps. Quiz data beats post-purchase guesswork.</p>
  <p>Postscript SMS at 80% window if email one unopened and checkout opt-in exists — one SMS per reorder cycle. Pet food and perishable categories see strongest SMS ROI; luxury beauty often email-only.</p>
  <p>Yotpo replenishment email with routine UGC — &quot;customers reorder this every 6 weeks&quot; social proof outperforms discount on email one for beauty replenishment.</p>
  <p>Marsello loyalty: show points earn on replenishment order in email one for enrolled profiles. Double-points promo must not collide with replenishment reminder same day — collision calendar.</p>
  <p>Wholesale and practitioner accounts excluded from DTC replenishment entirely. B2B reorder flows are separate playbook.</p>
  <p>Winback vs replenishment: lapsed 120+ days enters winback branch, not replenishment timer. Replenishment assumes recent buyer relationship.</p>
  <p>Holdout 10% on replenishment quarterly — consumable buyers often reorder on schedule without email. Prove incrementality before scaling volume.</p>

      <h2>Merchant scenarios</h2>
  <p><strong>Beauty serum replenishment:</strong> 42-day window → Yotpo routine UGC email one → one-tap reorder → 5% email two non-responders only → suppress Recharge subscribers.</p>
  <p><strong>Pet food by weight:</strong> Privy weight quiz → bag duration math → 80% trigger → SMS if unopened → multi-pet separate timers.</p>
  <p><strong>Protein subscription:</strong> Suppress replenishment on subscribed SKU → skip-save separate → one-time add-on replenishment valid.</p>
  <p><strong>Coffee consumption:</strong> Quiz household cups/day → bag size → 80% window → flavor cross-sell email two not discount.</p>

      <h2>Stack checklist</h2>
      <ul>
    <li>Per-SKU consumption windows documented</li>
    <li>80% and 100% trigger thresholds configured</li>
    <li>Recharge/Skio active subscriber suppression live</li>
    <li>Skip-flow separate from replenishment</li>
    <li>Full-price default on email one</li>
    <li>Bundle line-item tracking if applicable</li>
    <li>Privy quiz properties on profile</li>
    <li>Wholesale tags excluded</li>
    <li>Loyalty collision calendar checked</li>
    <li>SMS branch after email silence only</li>
    <li>Holdout cohort quarterly</li>
    <li>Replenishment margin tracked in Shopify</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Exclusions (non-negotiable)</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Customers who already reordered</li>
    <li>Subscription active on same SKU</li>
    <li>Products with irregular usage patterns</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Metrics that prove quality</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Replenishment conversion rate</li>
    <li>Days early/late vs optimal</li>
    <li>Subscription conversion from reminder</li>
    <li>Full-price replenishment rate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Common mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Universal 30-day reminder for all SKUs</li>
    <li>Discounting replenishment by default</li>
    <li>Ignoring subscription status</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Five-layer replenishment stack map</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>Consumption data: Privy, Shopify</h3>
    <p>Quiz properties and order line history feed timing math.</p>
    <p>Per-SKU window table maintained by ops.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Universal 30-day timer.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Three SKU categories have different live windows.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Lifecycle execution: Sequenzy</h3>
    <p>80%/100%/120% sequences with full-price default.</p>
    <p>Orchestrates subscription suppressions before send.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Discount-first every reminder.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Full-price replenishment rate above 60%.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Subscription gate: Klaviyo, Recharge</h3>
    <p>Active/skip/churn status suppressions.</p>
    <p>Zero replenishment to active same-SKU subscriber.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Promo conflicts with subscribe-and-save.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Monthly suppression audit.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>SMS layer: Postscript</h3>
    <p>Reorder window reminder after email silence.</p>
    <p>One SMS per cycle for pet/food/coffee opt-in cohorts.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Weekly SMS replenishment spam.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> SMS incremental reorder vs holdout.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Analytics: Shopify, Klaviyo</h3>
    <p>Replenishment conversion, full-price rate, holdout incrementality.</p>
    <p>Cohort by SKU category and acquisition source.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Revenue without subscription churn context.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Finance replenishment margin monthly.</p>
  </div>

      <h2>Timing and trigger governance</h2>
  <p>Primary trigger: 80% of consumption window per SKU.</p>
  <p>Follow-up: 100% depletion — stronger CTA, modest incentive cold segment only.</p>
  <p>Subscription upsell: 120% for non-subscribers who have reordered 2+ times.</p>
  <p>Never replenishment and promotional blast same day — collision calendar.</p>
  <p>Pause replenishment during active winback with better offer.</p>

      <h2>Measurement across the stack</h2>
  <p>Replenishment conversion rate per SKU category.</p>
  <p>Full-price replenishment percentage.</p>
  <p>Days early/late vs optimal consumption window.</p>
  <p>Subscription conversion from replenishment upsell at 120%.</p>
  <p>Holdout incrementality quarterly.</p>

      <h2>Related playbooks</h2>
  <p>Vertical: <a class="link" href="/for/beauty">beauty</a>, <a class="link" href="/for/supplements">supplements</a>, <a class="link" href="/for/pet-products">pet</a>.</p>
  <p>Related: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/winback">winback</a> for lapsed beyond replenishment window.</p>
  <p>Governance: <a class="link" href="/guides/loyalty-integration">loyalty integration</a>.</p>

<h2>Stack coordination for replenishment reminders</h2>
